Package ca.mcgill.ecse211.project

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BlockDetection
    This class is used to apply detection of blocks with an Ultrasonic and a Color Sensor.
    BlockPush
    This class contains push() method which will catch the block in front of the robot, navigate to the ramp and then push it to the bin.
    Correction
    This class is a helper class to correct the localization process.
    Gripper
    Gripper class is to control the motors for the gripper The class will have methods to revolve and grasp the target.
    LightLocalizer
    LightLocalizer class is used for getting a more precise localization.
    Main
    Main class of the program.
    Navigation
    The Navigation class is used to make the robot navigate around the playing field.
    Odometer
    The odometer class keeps track of the robot's (x, y, theta) deltaPosition.
    Resources
    Class for static resources (things that stay the same throughout the entire program execution), like constants and hardware.
    runUS
    This class will run the ultrasonic sensor and perform scanning.
    SmartRoutine
    The main movement class which with the obstacle avoidance feature.
    UltrasonicLocalizer
    UltrasonicLocalization class is used to get an approximation of robot heading via Ultrasonic Sensor.
    Walker
    This class includes key methods which let sensors to interfere the movement of the robot.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Resources.COLOR
    Your team color.
    UltrasonicLocalizer.LocalizationType
    The ultrasonic localization method can be implemented as a falling edge, rising edge.
